TY  - JOUR
AU  - Tiso, Maurizio
T1  - The Econometrics of Financial Markets
PY  - 1998
Y1  - 1998/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/11.1.0233
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 11
IS  - 1
SP  - 233
EP  - 238
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Written by three well-known scholars in the field, this text is an ambitious effort to elucidate a wide range of important topics in financial econometrics using an innovative combination of data analysis and sophisticated economic theory. For the first time, we have available in a single volume a large collection of topics previously found in specialized journals or advanced monographs only.Are asset returns predictable? Why are portfolio returns strongly positively autocorrelated when individual security returns are negatively correlated? Does the CAPM hold? How do we explain the large body of evidence that excess returns on stocks and other risky assets are predictable? These are just a few of the questions raised in the book for which an answer is provided or the state of the art presented.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/11.1.0233
ER  - 



